  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves multiple national and international laws and regulations designed to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes. Here are key components:\n\n1. International Frameworks\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. United States Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA)\n- Money Laundering Control Act\n- USA PATRIOT Act\n- Currency and Foreign Transactions Reporting Act\n\n3. Key Legal Requirements\n- Customer due diligence\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Record-keeping obligations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n\n4. Criminal Penalties\n- Significant financial fines\n- Asset seizure\n- imprisonment\n- Corporate and individual liability\n\n5. Regulatory Agencies\n- Financial Crimes Enforcement Network (FinCEN)\n- Department of Justice\n- Internal Revenue Service\n- Securities and Exchange Commission\n\n6. Compliance Mechanisms\n- Risk assessment\n- Internal control systems\n- Independent audits\n- Employee training programs\n\nThe framework aims to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds as legitimate income.",
